I know, I know, it's a Starbucks. But this one is different because  it has  much more room between the tables. Manager here is one of the nicest. Clean for the most part; manager & employees work hard at it--tho there is a lot of traffic. Ample free parking. Employees always get the order right.  Their mobile order pick-up area is sandwiched between the machines and register, so you may have to navigate your way carefully beyond the folks who are finalizing their purchase in store. More than once other customers have bumped into me as I'm picking up my mobile order, since some people immediately turn to their left from the register without looking, and a very few folks have been a little less than kind after walking into me while looking at their phones or wallet (guess we all need our coffee sometimes). However, their mobile order system is very good.  Bathroom available in store, but it is a one stall unisex bathroom. You can be in for a wait, and sometimes an unpleasant surprise once your turn comes. If you're very sensitive to those kinds of things, may be better to plan ahead and use the one in the complex, next to the Ba-Le sandwich shop. However, be warned that if you are a gold level member and have free refills available with Starbucks app, you will not be able to use that since you have technically left the shop.
